The paper focuses on the design and implementation of interactive lenses for immersive visualization environments, which is a topic that falls under the scope of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The lenses are used for the analysis of 3D sonar data, which involves graphics and visualization techniques (cs.GR, cs.GRAPHICS). The lenses are also manipulated and parameterized depending on the task, which suggests the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the lenses are designed for use in immersive environments, which suggests the use of virtual reality techniques (cs.VR).
